{"format": "tiptap/v1", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "HTML5 introduced a set of semantic sectioning and content elements that replace generic <div> and <span> containers with elements whose names describe their purpose. A page built from semantic elements is self-documenting: a browser, search engine, or screen reader can determine the role of each region without inspecting CSS class names. This topic maps every major semantic element, explains when to use it, and shows how Angular components integrate with the semantic document outline."}]}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "HTML semantic elements page structure map — header, nav, main, article, section, aside, figure, address, footer", "title": "HTML Semantic Page Structure"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why Semantic HTML Matters"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Accessibility.", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " Screen readers use landmark roles (derived from elements like <nav>, <main>, <aside>) to let users jump between page regions. Without them, keyboard users must tab through every link and button to find content."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "SEO.", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " Search engine crawlers weight content inside <article> and <main> more heavily and use <header>/<footer> content to understand page structure."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Maintainability.", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " <header class=\"site-header\"> communicates intent at a glance; <div class=\"site-header\"> does not. Semantics reduce the documentation burden."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Default browser styles.", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " <strong> is bold, <em> is italic, <blockquote> is indented — the browser's user-agent stylesheet provides a useful starting point."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Future-proofing.", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " Semantic elements carry meaning independent of any CSS framework. A refactor from Bootstrap to Tailwind does not break the document outline."}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Sectioning Elements"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Sectioning elements establish regions of the document that contribute to the accessibility tree's landmark navigation and the HTML document outline."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "header"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "<header> represents introductory content for its nearest sectioning ancestor. As a direct child of <body> it is the page header; inside <article> or <section> it is the article/section header."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "html"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "<!-- Page-level header -->\n<header>\n  <a href=\"/\" class=\"logo\"><img src=\"logo.svg\" alt=\"Acme Corp\" /></a>\n  <nav aria-label=\"Primary\">\n    <ul>\n      <li><a href=\"/products\">Products</a></li>\n      <li><a href=\"/pricing\">Pricing</a></li>\n      <li><a href=\"/about\">About</a></li>\n    </ul>\n  </nav>\n</header>\n\n<!-- Article-level header -->\n<article>\n  <header>\n    <h1>Understanding Angular Signals</h1>\n    <p>By Jane Doe · Published 2025-06-01 · 8 min read</p>\n  </header>\n  <!-- article body -->\n</article>\n"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "nav"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "<nav> marks a block of navigation links. A page may have multiple <nav> elements (primary navigation, breadcrumb, pagination); distinguish them with aria-label."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "html"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "<!-- Primary navigation -->\n<nav aria-label=\"Primary\">\n  <ul>\n    <li><a href=\"/\">Home</a></li>\n    <li><a href=\"/docs\">Docs</a></li>\n  </ul>\n</nav>\n\n<!-- Breadcrumb -->\n<nav aria-label=\"Breadcrumb\">\n  <ol>\n    <li><a href=\"/\">Home</a></li>\n    <li><a href=\"/docs\">Docs</a></li>\n    <li aria-current=\"page\">Signals</li>\n  </ol>\n</nav>\n\n<!-- Pagination -->\n<nav aria-label=\"Pagination\">\n  <a href=\"?page=1\" rel=\"prev\">Previous</a>\n  <a href=\"?page=3\" rel=\"next\">Next</a>\n</nav>\n"}]}, {"type": "blockquote", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Not every group of links warrants a <nav>. Footer lists of social icons or legal links are fine as plain <ul>. Reserve <nav> for primary navigation, breadcrumbs, and pagination — groups whose purpose is site navigation."}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "main"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "<main> contains the dominant content of the body — the thing the page is about. There must be exactly one visible <main> per page. It maps to the ARIA landmark role main, letting screen reader users jump directly to the content."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "html"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "<body>\n  <header>…</header>\n  <nav>…</nav>\n\n  <main id=\"main-content\">\n    <!-- skip link target -->\n    <h1>Page title</h1>\n    <p>Primary content here.</p>\n  </main>\n\n  <footer>…</footer>\n</body>\n"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "<main> should not be nested inside <article>, <aside>, <header>, <footer>, or <nav>."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Multiple <main> elements are allowed only if all but one are hidden (display:none or hidden attribute)."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Adding id=\"main-content\" enables a skip-link: <a href=\"#main-content\" class=\"skip-link\">Skip to content</a>."}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "article"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "<article> represents a self-contained piece of content that could be distributed independently — a blog post, a news item, a forum reply, a product card, or a comment. If you could syndicate it via RSS, it belongs in <article>."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "html"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "<article>\n  <header>\n    <h2><a href=\"/posts/angular-signals\">Understanding Angular Signals</a></h2>\n    <time datetime=\"2025-06-01\">June 1, 2025</time>\n  </header>\n\n  <p>Signals are a new reactivity primitive…</p>\n\n  <section>\n    <h3>Creating a signal</h3>\n    <pre><code>const count = signal(0);</code></pre>\n  </section>\n\n  <footer>\n    <p>Tagged: <a href=\"/tags/angular\">Angular</a>, <a href=\"/tags/signals\">Signals</a></p>\n  </footer>\n</article>\n"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "section"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "<section> represents a thematic grouping of content, typically with its own heading. Use it to partition a long article or a page into named chapters. Do not use <section> as a styling hook — that is what <div> is for."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "html"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "<article>\n  <h1>Angular Architecture Guide</h1>\n\n  <section>\n    <h2>Components</h2>\n    <p>Components are the building blocks…</p>\n  </section>\n\n  <section>\n    <h2>Services and Dependency Injection</h2>\n    <p>Services are singletons that…</p>\n  </section>\n\n  <section>\n    <h2>Routing</h2>\n    <p>The Angular Router…</p>\n  </section>\n</article>\n"}]}, {"type": "blockquote", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Every <section> should have a heading (h2–h6). If the section does not have a heading, consider whether <div> is more appropriate. The section element contributes to the document outline only when paired with a heading."}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "aside"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "<aside> marks content tangentially related to the surrounding content — a pull quote, a sidebar widget, a glossary term, an author bio, or a related-posts panel. Its ARIA landmark role is complementary."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "html"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "<main>\n  <article>\n    <h1>Angular vs React</h1>\n    <p>Both frameworks…</p>\n  </article>\n\n  <aside aria-label=\"Related resources\">\n    <h2>See also</h2>\n    <ul>\n      <li><a href=\"/angular-docs\">Official Angular docs</a></li>\n      <li><a href=\"/react-docs\">Official React docs</a></li>\n    </ul>\n  </aside>\n</main>\n"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "footer"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "<footer> represents closing content for its nearest sectioning ancestor. As a direct child of <body> it is the page footer (copyright, legal, social links); inside <article> or <section> it closes that specific section."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "html"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "<!-- Page footer -->\n<footer>\n  <nav aria-label=\"Footer\">\n    <a href=\"/privacy\">Privacy</a>\n    <a href=\"/terms\">Terms</a>\n    <a href=\"/contact\">Contact</a>\n  </nav>\n  <p><small>© 2025 Acme Corp. All rights reserved.</small></p>\n</footer>\n"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Content Semantic Elements"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Element", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Meaning", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Common use", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "<figure>"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Self-contained content referenced from the main flow"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Images with captions, code listings, charts, quotes"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "<figcaption>"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Caption for the parent <figure>"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Image credit, chart description, code listing title"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "<address>"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Contact information for nearest <article> or <body>"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Author email, physical address, social handle"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "<time>"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Machine-readable date/time"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Publish dates, event times (use datetime attribute)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "<mark>"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Text highlighted for reference"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Search result matches, highlighted terms"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "<abbr>"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Abbreviation or acronym"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "HTML, CSS, API — with title attribute for expansion"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "<cite>"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Title of a creative work"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Book title, film name, article title"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "<blockquote>"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Extended quotation from another source"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Quoted passages, testimonials"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "<details> + <summary>"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Disclosure widget — toggled open/closed"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "FAQ items, accordion without JavaScript"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "html"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "<!-- figure + figcaption -->\n<figure>\n  <img src=\"angular-architecture.png\" alt=\"Angular module dependency graph\" />\n  <figcaption>Fig 1 — Angular module dependency graph. Services are singletons per injector.</figcaption>\n</figure>\n\n<!-- figure with code -->\n<figure>\n  <pre><code>const count = signal(0);</code></pre>\n  <figcaption>Creating a signal with an initial value of 0.</figcaption>\n</figure>\n\n<!-- time with datetime attribute -->\n<p>Published <time datetime=\"2025-06-01\">June 1, 2025</time></p>\n<p>Meeting at <time datetime=\"14:30\">2:30 PM</time></p>\n\n<!-- address -->\n<address>\n  Written by <a href=\"mailto:jane@example.com\">Jane Doe</a><br />\n  <a href=\"https://example.com\">example.com</a>\n</address>\n\n<!-- details/summary — no JavaScript needed -->\n<details>\n  <summary>What is a signal in Angular?</summary>\n  <p>A signal is a reactive value that notifies consumers when it changes.</p>\n</details>\n\n<!-- mark, abbr, cite -->\n<p>\n  The <abbr title=\"Document Object Model\">DOM</abbr> spec is defined in\n  <cite>WHATWG HTML Living Standard</cite>.\n  Search results are <mark>highlighted</mark> in yellow.\n</p>\n"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "When to Use div and span"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "div and span remain valid — they are the correct choice when no semantic element fits."}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use case", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Choose", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Navigation links"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "<nav>"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Page-level header with logo"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "<header>"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Primary page content"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "<main>"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Self-contained syndicated content"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "<article>"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Thematic content grouping with heading"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "<section>"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Sidebar / tangential content"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "<aside>"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Closing content / copyright"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "<footer>"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Image with caption"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "<figure> + <figcaption>"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Generic block container (layout, JS hook, styling)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "<div>"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Generic inline container (styling, JS hook)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "<span>"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "blockquote", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "If you are reaching for <div> or <span> and a semantic element would communicate the same structure, prefer the semantic element. If you are styling or scripting a container with no inherent meaning, <div>/<span> is correct."}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Semantic HTML in Angular Components"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Angular components introduce custom element names (<app-header>, <app-card>) that browsers treat as generic inline elements. This makes it important to use semantic HTML inside component templates — the custom element itself carries no implicit landmark role."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Shell layout with semantic regions"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "typescript"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "// app.component.ts — root layout\n@Component({\n  selector: 'app-root',\n  standalone: true,\n  imports: [RouterOutlet, HeaderComponent, FooterComponent],\n  template: `\n    <a href=\"#main-content\" class=\"skip-link\">Skip to content</a>\n    <app-header />          <!-- <app-header> renders a <header> inside -->\n    <main id=\"main-content\">\n      <router-outlet />\n    </main>\n    <app-footer />          <!-- <app-footer> renders a <footer> inside -->\n  `,\n})\nexport class AppComponent {}\n"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "typescript"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "// header.component.ts — semantic element inside custom element\n@Component({\n  selector: 'app-header',\n  standalone: true,\n  template: `\n    <header>\n      <a routerLink=\"/\" class=\"logo\">\n        <img src=\"/assets/logo.svg\" alt=\"Acme Corp\" />\n      </a>\n      <nav aria-label=\"Primary\">\n        <ul>\n          <li><a routerLink=\"/products\" routerLinkActive=\"active\">Products</a></li>\n          <li><a routerLink=\"/about\" routerLinkActive=\"active\">About</a></li>\n        </ul>\n      </nav>\n    </header>\n  `,\n})\nexport class HeaderComponent {}\n"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Article component"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "typescript"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "// post-card.component.ts\n@Component({\n  selector: 'app-post-card',\n  standalone: true,\n  imports: [DatePipe, RouterLink],\n  template: `\n    <article>\n      <header>\n        <h2><a [routerLink]=\"['/posts', post.slug]\">{{ post.title }}</a></h2>\n        <p>\n          By {{ post.author }} ·\n          <time [attr.datetime]=\"post.publishedAt\">\n            {{ post.publishedAt | date:'mediumDate' }}\n          </time>\n        </p>\n      </header>\n      <p>{{ post.excerpt }}</p>\n      <footer>\n        <ul class=\"tags\">\n          @for (tag of post.tags; track tag) {\n            <li><a [routerLink]=\"['/tag', tag]\">#{{ tag }}</a></li>\n          }\n        </ul>\n      </footer>\n    </article>\n  `,\n})\nexport class PostCardComponent {\n  @Input({ required: true }) post!: Post;\n}\n"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Using host element semantics"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "If the component IS the semantic element (the component represents an article card), you can make the host element semantic using the host property instead of wrapping in an inner element."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "typescript"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "@Component({\n  selector: 'app-post-card',\n  standalone: true,\n  host: {\n    // Make the <app-post-card> host element act as <article>\n    role: 'article',\n    '[attr.aria-label]': 'post.title',\n  },\n  template: `\n    <header>\n      <h2>{{ post.title }}</h2>\n      <time [attr.datetime]=\"post.publishedAt\">{{ post.publishedAt | date }}</time>\n    </header>\n    <p>{{ post.excerpt }}</p>\n  `,\n})\nexport class PostCardComponent {\n  @Input({ required: true }) post!: Post;\n}\n"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Using role=\"article\" on the host element avoids the extra DOM wrapper, keeping the document outline clean."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Prefer this for leaf components that map 1:1 to a semantic element."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "For layout shells, keep the explicit semantic element inside the template for clarity."}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Heading Hierarchy and the Document Outline"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Screen readers provide a heading navigation shortcut (H key in most). A logical heading hierarchy lets users skim to relevant sections. The rule: h1 is the page title, h2 are major sections, h3 are subsections, and so on. Never skip levels (h1 → h3)."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "html"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "<!-- Correct hierarchy -->\n<h1>Angular Components Guide</h1>          <!-- page title, one per page -->\n  <h2>Component basics</h2>                <!-- major section -->\n    <h3>Creating a component</h3>          <!-- subsection -->\n    <h3>Component inputs</h3>\n  <h2>Lifecycle hooks</h2>\n    <h3>ngOnInit</h3>\n    <h3>ngOnDestroy</h3>\n  <h2>Change detection</h2>\n\n<!-- Within an article, you may restart from h1 -->\n<article>\n  <h1>Article title</h1>                   <!-- heading level resets in article -->\n    <h2>First section</h2>\n</article>\n"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use headings to convey structure, not to achieve visual size. Change visual size with CSS, not by picking a different heading level."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "In Angular, the component that renders the page <h1> is usually the routed page component — do not put a page-level <h1> in the shell layout."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "A page that uses <article> may use <h1> inside the article — the HTML5 specification allows this for nested sectioning elements, though browser support for the implied outline algorithm is inconsistent."}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Common Pitfalls"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Using <section> as a styled container.", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " <div class=\"card\"> is correct when there is no semantic meaning. <section class=\"card\"> misrepresents the element's role."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Multiple <main> elements visible simultaneously.", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " Only one <main> may be visible. If you toggle between views, hide inactive <main> elements with the hidden attribute."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Missing aria-label on multiple <nav> elements.", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " When more than one <nav> appears, screen readers announce \"navigation\" for each. Add aria-label=\"Primary\" / \"Footer\" / \"Breadcrumb\" to differentiate."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Nesting <header> or <footer> inside <header> or <footer>.", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " These elements cannot contain themselves. A <footer> inside a <header> is invalid HTML."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Using <article> for non-standalone content.", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " A general section of a marketing page is not an <article>. Use <section> or <div>."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Angular custom elements lack implicit roles.", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " <app-card> does not inherit the semantics of <article>. Use explicit semantic elements or the host.role property."}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Summary"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Semantic elements communicate purpose: <header>, <nav>, <main>, <article>, <section>, <aside>, <footer> create named landmarks that tools use for navigation."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "<header> and <footer> are scope-relative — they describe their nearest sectioning ancestor, not just the page."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "<nav> is for primary navigation links, breadcrumbs, and pagination — not every link group."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "<article> marks self-contained, distributable content; <section> marks a thematic grouping within a document or article."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "<figure> with <figcaption> is the correct pattern for images, code listings, and charts that need captions."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Headings (h1–h6) create the document outline; maintain a logical hierarchy without skipping levels."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "In Angular, semantic elements belong inside component templates — custom element names carry no implicit landmark roles."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use <div> and <span> for pure layout/styling containers; reach for a semantic element whenever one matches the content's meaning."}]}]}]}]}}